14
December
UBA Ghana Commences Branchless Banking

UBA Ghana has commenced the first of its kind branchless banking operation in Ghana at the Accra Shopping Mall.

The outlet christened the UBA E-Village provides customers with numerous card – based services for ease of transaction at the Mall. Customers can therefore load their funds unto a card and subsequently withdraw cash from the nearby ATM.

Similarly, customers can conveniently access UBA AFRICASH services, receive Western Union and MoneyGram remittances as well as pay for their electricity, water and DStv bills.

The UBA E-Village also provides customers the opportunity to send money to friends and family via MTN Mobile Money, Airtel Money or Tigo Cash in addition to paying for their Air Nigeria and Aero tickets amongst others.

With an average of 150,000 foot prints in the mall per week, this platform provides UBA Ghana with a unique opportunity to further increase UBA’s visibility and mind share for both our corporate brand and products  among our target market. 
 

12
December
Archbishop Palmer-Buckle visits UBA Ghana EXCO

The Metropolitan Catholic Archbishop of Accra, Most Reverend Charles Palmer-Buckle has advised the leadership of the bank not to operate a dormant account with God but build a strong relationship with him.

Archbishop Palmer-Buckle encouraged management that in the spirit of Christmas, UBA should give its best in terms of service delivery to its customers just as the three wise men gave their best when they went to worship the baby Jesus.

His Grace, Archbishop Palmer Buckle made the call when he recently joined EXCO for the last monthly EXCO Fellowship for 2011.
 
The fellowship initiated by the executive committee holds every first Monday of the month and is led by an invited senior member of the clergy.

The UBA EXCO Fellowship initiative has similarly hosted other senior members of the clergy such as Apostle General Sam Kuranchie Ankrah , Royal House Chapel International, Reverend Emmanuel Markwei, Livingstream Ministries and Reverend Gideon Titi- Ofei, SheepFold Chapel Accra.

14
November
UBA Pays Courtesy Call on President Mills

The President, Professor John Evans Atta Mills has called on banks in the country to increase their support for SME’s for the accelerated development of the Ghanaian economy.

The President made the call when a delegation from  United Bank for Africa (UBA) led by Mr. Gabriel Edgal, CEO UBA Africa, paid a courtesy call on him at the Castle, Osu.

The President lamented that though SME’s are the backbone of the economy they have increasingly faced challenges in accessing facilities from the banks.

President Mills mentioned that support for the SME’s will inure to the benefit of the country through the creation of employment opportunities and increased revenue to the nation.

Mr. Edgal informed the President about the banks activities across Africa and Ghana in particular while giving the assurance that UBA will continue to assist in the development of the local economy.

22
June
UBA Walks Against Prostate Cancer

Alarmed about the incidence of Prostate Cancer in Ghana, The United Bank for Africa (UBA) Ghana limited has joined the fight against prostate cancer in Ghana.

The African Bank announced that it is going engage in organizing free testing of Prostate Cancer exercise across the country. The MD/CEO, Mr Oliver Alawuba made this known at the bank’s 9th health walk dubbed “Walk-Jog-Cycle against Prostate Cancer”.

The walk which was second in this year but ninth in its series was used to create awareness of prostate cancer in the country.statisics shows that every year 950 Ghanaian men are diagnosed with the disease while every man who in Ghana is at risk of the cancer.

Mr Alawuba who led the walk espoused the banks commitment to the fight against Prostate Cancer.

A medical Doctor of the Soyuz Medical Imaging and Diagnostics limited Dr, Victor Dedjoe educated staff and journalists on the symptoms and dangers of the disease and advised Ghanaians to be health cautious.

The event which took place at the Ghana International School in Accra was concurrently held in UBA’s regions of operation and 19 African countries.
 

03
June
UBA Ghana Appoints New Managing Director/CEO
The Board of United Bank for Africa (Ghana) Limited, has appointed Mr. Oliver Alawuba as the new Chief Executive Officer of the bank following the elevation of the immediate past CEO, Mr. Gabriel Edgal to the position of Chief Executive, UBA West Africa.

Mr. Oliver Alawuba has over twenty years experience in investment banking, retail and commercial banking, corporate finance as well as project management. He has worked with some major African banks in various managerial capacities including being Regional Director, South Central Region of Standard Trust Bank Limited now United Bank for Africa Nigeria PLC and Executive Director of Finbank Nigeria PLC for South South and South East Regions covering over 11 States in Nigeria.

Until his appointment, Mr. Alawuba was the MD/CEO Designate of UBA Cote D’Ivoire. He holds a Masters degree in Banking and Finance from the Ogun State University, Ago Iwoye, Nigeria as well as an Msc. in Food Technology from the University of Ibadan. He is an alumnus of the SEP and AMP programmes at the London Business School and Insead Business School respectively.
13
April
Read Africa Initiative

A high powered delegation of officials of UBA led by the CEO, UBA West Africa, recently donated UBA branded reading materials to selected institutions within the Accra Metropolis.

Mr. Edgal, CEO, UBA West Africa in presenting the books to the Headmistress on behalf of the students of the Ridge Church School in Accra, challenged the children to take their reading very seriously. He stated that “bridging the gap between the Diaspora and Africa will only occur through the adoption of a comprehensive reading culture so as to be abreast with happenings in the world.
He counseled that “as students your future will be determined and shaped by the quality of books your read today therefore I urge you to pay a serious attention to reading for a brighter future”.
Mr. Edgal also paid glowing tribute to teachers for their immeasurable contribution to the development of the leaders of tomorrow and urged them not to relent in their efforts.

At the Mary Mother of Good Council School, Mr Oliver Alawuba MD/CEO, Ghana, entreated the highly elated students of the school not to rest on their oars in the pursuit of their dreams. He advised the children to turn to their books instead of the digital entertainment gadgets while adding that to achieve the dreams they have set for themselves it was important they cultivated a reading habit now. “Reading is the only way your dreams of becoming bankers, lawyers, pharmacists and doctors will materialize” Mr. Alawuba advised.

Other members of the delegation were Oliver Alawuba, MD/CEO UBA Ghana, Chioma Mang, MD/CEO UBA Liberia and Adesipo Adedayo, COO, UBA Ghana.

The regional directors also led delegations to make similar donations to schools across Takoradi, Kumasi, Tema and Aflao.

05
April
UBA Ghana Launches Western Union Partnership

United Bank for Africa has entered into partnership with Western Union to offer cross-border money transfer services for inward remittances. This brings to four the international money transfer services UBA offers:
Within Africa

  • Africash
  • Afritrade

From the rest of the world

  • Western Union
  • Moneygram

Speaking at the official launch of the partnership, Mr. Gabriel Edgal, MD/CEO of UBA Ghana, mentioned that the ever increasing rate of Ghanaians and people of African descent to work outside their countries has made it inevitable for them to send money back to their families in their home countries for subsistence or to build up of capital for use when they return. Hence the addition of Western Union to UBA’s array of money transfer services is yet another manifestation of the bank’s responsiveness to the needs of its customers.

Mr. Edgal said the Bank’s vision of democratizing banking in Ghana and Africa triggered the need to come out with products and services that would help deepen financial intermediation on the continent. “As a pan-African bank, UBA provides the platform needed to transact business that is why we introduced Afritrade and Africash to facilitate trade on the continent and also to help families to remit money.”

“In order to achieve our goal of becoming a major player in the international money transfer market, UBA needed to partner with the global leader in International Money Transfer hence our decision to sign on to the Western Union Money Transfer Service”, he added.

Mr. Daniel Addo the Executive Director of the Bank remarked that “this addition not only reinforces the Bank’s leadership in the money transfer industry but aligns with UBA’s determination to always delight its customers through excellent service delivery”.

UBA (Ghana) Limited is a subsidiary of the United Bank for Africa PLC which is West Africa’s largest financial services group with assets in excess of US$20 billion and offering services to more than 7.5 million customers across 750 branches and over 2000 Visa enabled ATMs in 19 African countries
 

24
January
UBA Launches Super Saver Loyalty Card

UBA (GH) in partnership with Melcom Group of Companies owners of the Melcom retail chain in Ghana yesterday introduced the first ever loyalty card for shoppers in the country at the Melcom Plus Shopping centre in Accra, Ghana.

The card christened MELCOM/UBA SUPER SAVER CARD can be used to purchase any item from any Melcom shop nationwide.

Mr Ramesh Sadhwani, Joint Group Managing Director of Melcom Group of Companies mentioned in his welcome address that " the idea of the Melcom/UBA Super Saver card is to make the shopping experience of our customers more convenient, in addition to giving them added advantages" in his presentation, Executive Director of UBA, Ghana, Mr Daniel Addo, stated that in addition to the many features of the card, funds can easily be accessed 24/7 from any UBA POS/ATM nationwide.

Launching the card, Mr Gabriel Edgal, MD/CEO of UBA Ghana, demonstrated how the card operates to the invited guest and the media who were in attendance.
